header.gameNote: RAINBOW WAHINE CLASSIC AT HONOLULU HI

article.headline: (17) DEPAUL 76, WISCONSIN 57
article.story:
HONOLULU (AP) -- Khara Smith had 24 points and 10 rebounds to
help DePaul beat Wisconsin 76-57 in the championship game of the
Rainbow Wahine Classic on Sunday night.

The 17th-ranked Blue Demons (5-0) used a 15-2 run to extend a
three-point halftime lead and put the game out of reach.

Danielle Ward's basket ended Wisconsin's four-minute scoring
drought with 13:20 remaining but the Badgers failed to shrink the
margin against DePaul to less than 13 points the rest of the game.

Smith shot 11 of 16 from the field and earned tournament MVP
honors. She also posted double-doubles in wins over Eastern
Michigan and Texas A&M in the tournament.

Jenna Rubino scored 17 points, including five 3-pointers for
DePaul. Allie Quigley added 14 points.

Janese Banks had 17 points and eight rebounds and Jolene
Anderson added 12 points for Wisconsin.

The Badgers (4-1) were 17 of 20 from the free throw line.
